From: Johannes Thumshirn <jthumshirn@suse.de>
Date: Mon, 9 Apr 2018 14:39:22 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] scsi: qla2xxx: Correct setting of SAM_STAT_CHECK_CONDITION
References: bsc#1094555
Git-commit: 584d7aad28fd5251a72d3efb3ba76284f3a670fd
Patch-mainline: v4.17-rc1

Bart reports that in qla_isr.c's qla2x00_handle_dif_error we're wrongly
shifting the SAM_STAT_CHECK_CONDITION by one instead of directly ORing it
onto the SCSI command's result.

Signed-off-by: Johannes Thumshirn <jthumshirn@suse.de>
Reported-by: Bart Van Assche <Bart.VanAssche@wdc.com>
Cc: Himanshu Madhani <himanshu.madhani@cavium.com>
Reviewed-by: Hannes Reinecke <hare@suse.com>
Reviewed-by: Bart Van Assche <bart.vanassche@wdc.com>
Signed-off-by: Martin K. Petersen <martin.petersen@oracle.com>
Signed-off-by: Hannes Reinecke <hare@suse.de>
---
 drivers/scsi/qla2xxx/qla_isr.c | 6 +++---
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/scsi/qla2xxx/qla_isr.c b/drivers/scsi/qla2xxx/qla_isr.c
index 4d2a81f5cd12..42f0ed30ffaa 100644
--- a/drivers/scsi/qla2xxx/qla_isr.c
+++ b/drivers/scsi/qla2xxx/qla_isr.c
@@ -2177,7 +2177,7 @@ qla2x00_handle_dif_error(srb_t *sp, struct sts_entry_24xx *sts24)
 		    0x10, 0x1);
 		set_driver_byte(cmd, DRIVER_SENSE);
 		set_host_byte(cmd, DID_ABORT);
-		cmd->result |= SAM_STAT_CHECK_CONDITION << 1;
+		cmd->result |= SAM_STAT_CHECK_CONDITION;
 		return 1;
 	}
 
@@ -2187,7 +2187,7 @@ qla2x00_handle_dif_error(srb_t *sp, struct sts_entry_24xx *sts24)
 		    0x10, 0x3);
 		set_driver_byte(cmd, DRIVER_SENSE);
 		set_host_byte(cmd, DID_ABORT);
-		cmd->result |= SAM_STAT_CHECK_CONDITION << 1;
+		cmd->result |= SAM_STAT_CHECK_CONDITION;
 		return 1;
 	}
 
@@ -2197,7 +2197,7 @@ qla2x00_handle_dif_error(srb_t *sp, struct sts_entry_24xx *sts24)
 		    0x10, 0x2);
 		set_driver_byte(cmd, DRIVER_SENSE);
 		set_host_byte(cmd, DID_ABORT);
-		cmd->result |= SAM_STAT_CHECK_CONDITION << 1;
+		cmd->result |= SAM_STAT_CHECK_CONDITION;
 		return 1;
 	}
 
